==English==

===Noun===
'''esky'''  (''plural:'' '''[[eskies]]''')
# (Australia) an [[insulated]] picnic [[cooler]], using [[refrigerated]] blocks to keep food cool.

===Usage note===
Esky is a [[brand]] name of the Nylex Corporation, but the word is commonly used to name any type of cooler.

===Pronunciation===
''es kee'' , (pl) ''es kees''.

